  "original_title": "\u0baa\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf \u0b9c\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0ba4\u0bc6\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b9c\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf  \u0bb0\u0ba3\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b86\u0ba4\u0bb0\u0bb5\u0bc1  - \u0bb8\u0bcd\u0bb0\u0bc0\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbe \u0baa\u0bca\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b9c\u0ba9 \u0baa\u0bc6\u0bb0\u0bae\u0bc1\u0ba9",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Support for President Ranil in New Presidential Election - Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna",
      "author": "Vishnu",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna has officially decided to support President Ranil Wickremesinghe in the parliamentary poll for the new President; The party's general secretary Sagara Kariyawasam said that he will not support former minister Dalus Alagaperuma.",
        "Members of Podujana Peramuna will support Acting President Ranil Wickremesinghe during the vote for the new President.",
        "This decision was officially taken after Member of Parliament Dallas Alagaperuma announced that he will contest for the new presidential election to be held in Parliament next Wednesday.",
        "Dallas Alagaperuma has mentioned that he is ready to contest in the parliamentary vote for the election of the President. He has not decided to support him as a party.",
        "He said that it was decided to provide support to the President because the current President should take the next step in order to solve the economic crisis without political factors.",
        "Former minister Dulles Alagapperuma, who contested in the Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna's budding party in the 2020 general election and was elected to parliament, has stated that he is ready to contest in the 'vacant executive power of the president' and has sought the support of all members of parliament.",
        "In the 2020 general election, the Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna won 59.09 percent of the votes and captured all 145 seats in the Parliament. Sri Lanka Freedom Party, Sri Lanka Workers Congress, including Wimal Weerawansa, Udaya Kammanpila, Vasudeva Nanayakkara, Thissa Vidharana announced that they left the government on April 5th and are working independently in the Parliament. Even though the number of independents in the Parliament was found to be 44, some of them joined the government and got ministerial posts.",
        "However, Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna currently has more than 113 seats in the Parliament and it has been confirmed on various occasions. The 10 political parties operating independently in Parliament and only five including Anura Priyadarshana Yappa and Sudarshani Fernando Pulle initially indicated that they would cooperate with Podujana Peramuna's member Dussel Alagaperuma, although they did not officially mention it."
      ],
